      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:19:1",
      "text": [
        " النَّفْيُ مِنْ بَلْدَةٍ إِلَى بَلْدَةٍ وَ قَالَ قَدْ نَفَى عَلِيٌّ ( صلوات الله عليه ) رَجُلَيْنِ مِنَ الْكُوفَةِ إِلَى الْبَصْرَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The exiling is from a city to a city’. And he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Ali<sup>asws</sup> had exiled two men from Al-Kufa to Al-Basra’."
        ]
      }
